time for another baby okay so here is my story i am an army wife and we are about to be moving to another state a base in alaska i have one child who is months old my husband and i always talked about having two children but we are both very happy with the way things are going right now he asked me last night where are we at on having another baby i was a little stunned but we talked about it and he wanted to know how i was feeling about it i am several years older than he is i am and he is he knows that i have always said i wanted to have our children close together because i don't want to be mid 's having an infant part of me feels like i am completely happy having only one child and the other part thinks it would be wonderful for her to have a sibling we will be moving in december and there is the possibility he will be going back to iraq after we get there that scares me because i will be raising babies alone instead of just one i am looking for opinions thanks for your answers having one child and being a single parent even temporarily such as during a long deployment is tough it's even tougher with more children if you're both happy with one just have the one there are many positives to being an only child EastEnders Knots Landing Humphrey Bogart Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Baby Blues Abortion debate Cliff Richard Adoption Shaggy dog story The Beatles discography Sunset Beach (soap opera) Laura Schlessinger Avenue Q Breastfeeding The Amber Spyglass Jon Secada Fiddler on the Roof Kodocha The Ashlee Simpson Show The Emancipation of Mimi Infantilism Infidels Rais massacre Friends History of As the World Turns (2000-present) Pitaten Plame affair Miss Saigon Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Grandview, U.S.A. Sharon Tate Cindy Sheehan Time Out of Mind Episodes of Lost (Season 1) U.S. 82nd Airborne Division Too Short a Season (TNG episode) Generation Y The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Transactional analysis Cool (song) Smallville (Season 4) Child s